{"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"GIO"}],"title":"close(cancellable:)","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"close","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"cancellable"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO14CancellableRefV","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"CancellableRef"},{"kind":"text","text":"?) "},{"text":"throws","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" -> ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"roleHeading":"Instance Method","symbolKind":"method","extendedModule":"GIO","externalID":"s:3GIO16IOStreamProtocolPAAE5close11cancellableSbAA14CancellableRefVSg_tKF::SYNTHESIZED::s:3GIO23TcpWrapperConnectionRefV"},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TcpWrapperConnectionRef\/close(cancellable:)"},"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/tcpwrapperconnectionref\/close(cancellable:)"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"close"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"text":"cancellable","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO14CancellableRefV","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/CancellableRef","text":"CancellableRef","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"? = nil) ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"keyword","text":"throws"},{"text":" -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"content":[{"anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Once the stream is closed, all other operations will return"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"closed","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". Closing a stream multiple times will not"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"return an error.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Closing a stream will automatically flush any outstanding buffers","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"in the stream."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Streams will be automatically closed when the last reference","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"is dropped, but you might want to call this function to make sure"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"resources are released as early as possible.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Some streams might keep the backing store of the stream (e.g. a file"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"descriptor) open after the stream is closed. See the documentation for"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the individual stream for details."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"On failure the first error that happened will be reported, but the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"close operation will finish as much as possible. A stream that failed","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to close will still return "},{"code":"closed","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" for all operations."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Still, it is important to check and report the error to the user,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"otherwise there might be a loss of data as all data might not be written."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If "},{"code":"cancellable","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is not NULL, then the operation can be cancelled by","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"triggering the cancellable object from another thread. If the operation"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"was cancelled, the error "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"cancelled"},{"text":" will be returned.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Cancelling a close will still leave the stream closed, but some streams","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"can use a faster close that doesn’t block to e.g. check errors.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The default implementation of this method just calls close on the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"individual input\/output streams.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Closes the stream, releasing resources related to it. This will also"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"close the individual input and output streams, if they are not already","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"closed."}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TcpWrapperConnectionRef","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TcpWrapperConnectionRef\/IOStreamProtocol-Implementations"]]},"kind":"symbol","references":{"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/SocketConnection":{"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"SocketConnection","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"SocketConnection","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SocketConnection","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/socketconnection","abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GSocketConnection"},{"type":"text","text":" is a [class"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/IOStream","isActive":true},{"text":"] for a connected socket. They","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"can be created either by [class"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SocketClient","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"] when connecting to a host,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"or by [class","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SocketListener","type":"reference"},{"text":"] when accepting a new client.","type":"text"}],"title":"SocketConnection"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/CancellableRef":{"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"CancellableRef","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"CancellableRef","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/CancellableRef","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/cancellableref","abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GCancellable"},{"type":"text","text":" allows operations to be cancelled."}],"title":"CancellableRef"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/IOStream":{"url":"\/documentation\/gio\/iostream","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/IOStream","title":"IOStream","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"IOStream","kind":"identifier"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"IOStream"}],"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GIOStream"},{"type":"text","text":" represents an object that has both read and write streams."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Generally the two streams act as separate input and output streams,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"but they share some common resources and state. For instance, for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"seekable streams, both streams may use the same position."}],"type":"topic","role":"symbol"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/TcpWrapperConnectionRef/close(cancellable:)":{"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TcpWrapperConnectionRef\/close(cancellable:)","title":"close(cancellable:)","role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"close","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"text":"cancellable","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO14CancellableRefV","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"CancellableRef"},{"text":"?) ","kind":"text"},{"text":"throws","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb"}],"url":"\/documentation\/gio\/tcpwrapperconnectionref\/close(cancellable:)","abstract":[{"text":"Closes the stream, releasing resources related to it. This will also","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"close the individual input and output streams, if they are not already"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"closed.","type":"text"}]},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/TcpWrapperConnectionRef/IOStreamProtocol-Implementations":{"type":"topic","kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TcpWrapperConnectionRef\/IOStreamProtocol-Implementations","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/tcpwrapperconnectionref\/iostreamprotocol-implementations","abstract":[],"title":"IOStreamProtocol Implementations","role":"collectionGroup"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/TcpWrapperConnectionRef":{"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"TcpWrapperConnectionRef","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"TcpWrapperConnectionRef","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TcpWrapperConnectionRef","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/tcpwrapperconnectionref","abstract":[{"text":"A ","type":"text"},{"code":"GTcpWrapperConnection","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" can be used to wrap a [class"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/IOStream","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"] that is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"based on a [class"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Socket"},{"type":"text","text":"], but which is not actually a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[class"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SocketConnection","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"]. This is used by [class"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SocketClient"},{"text":"] so","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"that it can always return a [class","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SocketConnection","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"], even when the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"connection it has actually created is not directly a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[class"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SocketConnection","isActive":true},{"text":"].","type":"text"}],"title":"TcpWrapperConnectionRef"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/SocketClient":{"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"SocketClient"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SocketClient","abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GSocketClient"},{"type":"text","text":" is a lightweight high-level utility class for connecting to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a network host using a connection oriented socket type."}],"title":"SocketClient","role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/socketclient","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"SocketClient"}]},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/Socket":{"type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Socket"}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Socket","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/socket","abstract":[{"text":"A ","type":"text"},{"code":"GSocket","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is a low-level networking primitive. It is a more or less"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"direct mapping of the BSD socket API in a portable GObject based API."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"It supports both the UNIX socket implementations and winsock2 on Windows.","type":"text"}],"title":"Socket","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Socket","kind":"identifier"}]},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO":{"type":"topic","abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","title":"GIO","url":"\/documentation\/gio","role":"collection","kind":"symbol"}}}